&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Area of work&lt;/span&gt; Administration/Reception&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Job Title Administration Officer / Senior Receptionist (&lt;/span&gt;Calder Community Practice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Job Location&lt;/span&gt; Calder Community Practice, Todmorden Health Centre (&lt;em&gt;Locala Community Partnerships CIC&lt;/em&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Salary: £19,737 to £21,142 Band 3 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hours Per Week: 37.5 – Part time/Job Share will be considered&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Job Type: Permanent &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Reference: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date: Sunday 15&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Calder Community Practice is a GP practice located on the second floor in the Todmorden Health Centre, Todmorden bus services and train station are within 5 minutes walking distance. There is some free car parking available in and around the centre.All doctors, advanced nurse practitioners, practice nurses and staff are committed to providing an outstanding, family-friendly service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We require a highly motivated and proactive Band 3Administration Officer / Senior Receptionist to join us.The post holder will be an excellent communicator both face to face and on the phone, confident, enthusiastic and eager to learn. Previous experience of working in a primary care GP Practice essential. You will be a team player and happy to join our busy administration support team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of this team you will be responsible for registering patients and updating records on relevant systems, managing requests from other colleagues, answer a busy phone line, using online booking system (SystmOne) and have good all-round administration experience.Supervision of junior members of staff as appropriate in accordance with the policies and procedures of Locala. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The service is open Monday to Friday 08.00hr to 18.30 hrs but additional weekend/evening work may be required in line with the NHS Primary Care Networks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return for becoming part of our team we offer a full induction and training package to support your needs, we will develop and motivate you to enable you to have the right skills to do your job, we offer great working conditions along with supporting you to achieve a good work life balance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information about the role please contact Gordon Johnson, Business Manager on 030 3330 9158.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
